I’m nearing the state of being corona’d out. On our radio show this morning, I sent an instruction to our news team to limit virus-related news and try to include reports on other things. They responded that, despite trying, it was impossible. As addicted as we may be to knowing what is going on, sifting through the information, real and not, is becoming increasingly too much. People keep asking me in disbelief whether government’s actions are legitimate, so I have to try to stay abreast – so much so that I watched a 20-minute news story over the weekend from...